Just pinging you about this PR in case you hadn't seen it. According to the [official docs](https://github.com/prestodb/presto/wiki/HTTP-Protocol), insofar as you can call them that, the nextUri may or may not be present on any response, and one should just rely on the `error` field to determine whether there has been an error. As far as I can see there is no mention of `nextUri` being missing for errors. This is only masking error messages for true issues, so it is at least not preventing queries from succeeding, but it has made it hard to diagnose some users' issues.

