> Could you give us some idea what is in this `config.yaml`? 

`config.yaml` in my preliminary implementation corresponds to `compiler.yaml` in the above description. The file is automatically generated and installed by the compiler recipe's `build.sh/bld.bat` scripts and simply defines a number of jinja2 variables. For example, the `visual-studio-build-14.0` recipe would create a `$CONDA_ACTIVE_ENV/conda-meta/features/compiler.yaml` file that looks like this:
```
{% set name='visual-studio' %}
{% set version='14.0' %}
{% set feature='vc14' %}
{% set version_tag='.vc14' %}
{% set build_requirement='visual-studio-build 14.0' %}
{% set run_requirement='visual-studio 14.0' %}
```

> I have seen some other files being imported in other recipes there. What do these different files offer?

These files are unrelated to conda features and define a number of variables (e.g. the path to the compiler) and convenience functions (e.g. to convert between Linux and Windows paths) that are useful in `bld.bat` scripts.

